            <thetext>If the loading of the tests is failing we show a message at the bottom of the Test Runner

&quot;System Status: Invalid test file selected!&quot;

However, this message is at the bottom of the Test Runner and can hardly be recognized. The user only looks at the spinner loading indicator.

Since the Test Runner is an invalid state if the tests are not loaded correctly we should show a more prominent feedback e.g. an alert box.

This is an issue if the developer generates the &quot;test-source&quot; version and loads the &quot;normal&quot; test runner (=&gt; &quot;index.html&quot;) and vice versa. The developer does load the &quot;index-source.html&quot; file and generated the &quot;test&quot; job only.</thetext>
